cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial examples, which is a well-known problem in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes guidelines for evaluating future defenses, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
